Q1. Phishing Simulation [10M]
Objective: Create and conduct a simulation to test user awareness.

Steps:

Planning

Define scope: All employees or a specific department.

Choose platform: Use tools like GoPhish, KnowBe4, or a manual email setup.

Set timeline: One-day campaign or staggered over a week.

Design Phishing Email

Make it realistic: Use urgency, spoofed sender (e.g., “IT Support”), and a fake login page.

Example: “Your password expires in 24 hours. Click here to keep the same password.”

Include a tracked link to monitor clicks.

Conduct Simulation

Send emails without prior notification.

Track:

Emails opened

Links clicked

Credentials entered (if using a fake login page)

Reported as phishing (if a report button is available)

Ethical & Safety Measures

Inform HR/management in advance.

Ensure fake landing page does not store actual credentials.

Provide immediate redirect to a training page after click.

