Q2. Analyze Results & Generate Report [15M]
Objective: Present findings and recommend improvements.

Report Structure:

Executive Summary

Total recipients: e.g., 200

Click rate: e.g., 35% (70 users)

Credential submission: e.g., 15% (30 users)

Reported rate: e.g., 5% (10 users)

Detailed Findings

Open Rate: % who opened the email — indicates subject line effectiveness.

Click Rate: % who clicked the link — shows susceptibility.

Credential Entry Rate: % who submitted data — highest risk.

Reporting Rate: % who flagged email — measures security culture.

Segmentation (Optional)

Compare departments, seniority, or office locations to identify high-risk groups.

Analysis

High click rate suggests need for better awareness of phishing indicators.

Low reporting rate indicates lack of confidence or no clear reporting process.

Recommendations

Mandatory phishing awareness training for high-risk users.

Implement a “Report Phishing” button in email clients.

Conduct quarterly simulations with varying difficulty levels.

Reward users who report phishing attempts.

Conclusion

Summarize current risk level and planned next steps.

